Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.92,0:00:50.21,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come home soon, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.34,0:00:58.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, shut up! Stop ringing!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.93,0:01:02.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, already...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.10,0:01:07.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was up until late last night, \Nso just a few more minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.02,0:01:10.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, you're heartless!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.72,0:01:39.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. That pendant...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.36,0:01:54.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It hasn't begun yet, but I can't \Nbe too careful, can I?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.12,0:02:11.50,Title,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(299,494)}#00  Prologue
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.35,0:02:22.68,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.68,0:02:24.74,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see a single student...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.18,0:02:27.19,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's too quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.61,0:02:36.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess it's just one of those days.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.54,0:02:45.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Tohsaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.20,0:02:47.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're early today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.21,0:02:51.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, so that's it...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.96,0:02:56.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.84,0:02:58.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sure is cold today, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.47,0:02:59.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Mitsuzuri-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.59,0:03:04.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, do you know what time it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.85,0:03:07.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The time? It's just before seven, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.10,0:03:09.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka, are you half-asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.81,0:03:12.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like the clocks at home were an hour fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.65,0:03:18.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not only my alarm clock, but the wall \Nclocks, too. By exactly one hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.53,0:03:22.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It happened right after I found the pendant...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.45,0:03:24.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Could Father have caused it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.20,0:03:27.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.58,0:03:30.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Holding morning practice again, Mitsuzuri-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.87,0:03:33.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I lost one of our best people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.92,0:03:37.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have to try to put on a good show \Nso new students will join our club.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.96,0:03:41.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When you're team captain, \Nit's always something, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.26,0:03:44.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, since you're here, why not watch our practice?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.52,0:03:52.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You really don't want to watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.44,0:03:54.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know anything about archery.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.40,0:03:56.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So watching from a distance will be good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.74,0:04:04.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.95,0:04:07.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, good morning, Matou.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.46,0:04:09.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is it just you this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.00,0:04:10.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.16,0:04:13.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry that I wasn't able to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.42,0:04:15.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine, don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.04,0:04:18.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If someone isn't into it, there's no point \Nin forcing them to participate.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.92,0:04:20.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be going, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.84,0:04:23.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,See you later, Mitsuzuri-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.05,0:04:25.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. Later, Tohsaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.64,0:04:29.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for visiting, Tohsaka-senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.69,0:04:32.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.94,0:04:34.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Work hard, Sakura.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.53,0:04:41.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Tohsaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.74,0:04:42.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.24,0:04:45.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I must be lucky, running into \Nyou first thing in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.08,0:04:49.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Matou Shinji-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.12,0:04:50.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're here early this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.70,0:04:51.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.87,0:04:53.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm team captain, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.42,0:04:56.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Assistant manager, more like...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.50,0:04:57.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.04,0:04:59.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.17,0:05:01.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You should sit in on our morning practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.09,0:05:02.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.51,0:05:05.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to get in the way of practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.14,0:05:07.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No one will mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.39,0:05:10.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My point is that I don't want to be a bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.60,0:05:14.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I'm not all that interested in archery.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.94,0:05:16.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.69,0:05:19.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.15,0:05:22.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I had the wrong idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.68,0:05:26.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you kept coming to watch after-school \Npractices because you were interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.87,0:05:30.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? You were there to watch \Nsomething else, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.29,0:05:36.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stay away from me, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.65,0:05:40.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let me be clear, Matou-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.75,0:05:46.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not only am I not interested in archery, \NI'm not interested in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.30,0:05:50.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The fact is that I only just now noticed \Nyou were on the archery range,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.56,0:05:52.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and I'm certain I won't notice you in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.73,0:05:54.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.93,0:05:57.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you, Tohsaka?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.44,0:06:02.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're welcome to be self-conscious, \Nbut you should tone it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.11,0:06:05.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, if it isn't Tohsaka-san! Morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.82,0:06:08.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Fujimura-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.83,0:06:16.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.62,0:06:19.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if it isn't the student council president.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.63,0:06:22.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Patrolling the campus so early in the morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.38,0:06:25.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or are you making maintenance \Nrounds of the club rooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.38,0:06:28.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not that I care either way. \NStill, you're the diligent student as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.30,0:06:32.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And what do you have up your sleeve?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.18,0:06:35.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you here so early, \Nwhen you aren't in any clubs?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.43,0:06:37.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I just felt like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.52,0:06:42.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I fixed it, Issei.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.44,0:06:43.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.98,0:06:48.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I asked you for help, but you \Ndid it all, Emiya. My bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.28,0:06:49.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the next one?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.91,0:06:51.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have a lot of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.05,0:06:54.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The next one's in the A/V room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.16,0:06:59.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They say it's been acting up lately, but it's \Nfinally exhausted its lifespan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.25,0:07:03.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If it's dead, I can't fix that. \NBuying a new one would be faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.71,0:07:07.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's true, but I'd appreciate it if you \Ncould take a look at it anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.34,0:07:11.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It looked dead to me, but you may be able \Nto see if it's just faking or really dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.26,0:07:14.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll try...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.85,0:07:21.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're here early, Tohsaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.07,0:07:27.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Was that his way of saying hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.13,0:07:49.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,E-Excuse me, Tohsaka-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.13,0:07:51.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't mind, would you \Nlike to eat lunch together?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.26,0:07:55.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Saegusa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.31,0:07:58.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but I'm going to the cafeteria today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.87,0:08:01.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I overslept this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.52,0:08:03.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you did?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.48,0:08:07.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know. I'm sorry for stopping you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.15,0:08:10.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let this discourage you. \NFeel free to ask me again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.95,0:08:11.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.95,0:08:14.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, I had no idea that you were \Ncapable of oversleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.58,0:08:18.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I oversleep all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.33,0:08:21.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not in any clubs because \NI can't get out of bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.04,0:08:24.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, enjoy your lunch, Saegusa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.38,0:08:26.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will. You, too, Tohsaka-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.75,0:08:29.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you got shot down, Yukicchi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.09,0:08:31.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.55,0:08:34.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka never brings a boxed lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.22,0:08:38.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Maki, all we need to do is eat \Nlunch in the cafeteria, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.68,0:08:41.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.06,0:08:43.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Try sitting with Tohsaka sometime!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.19,0:08:45.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's so annoying, the way \Nyou can feel guys staring!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.52,0:08:51.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When she and I went out last weekend, \Nshe reaped all the benefits!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.82,0:08:56.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Makinoji, it looks like Tohsaka can hear \Nyou talking about her behind her back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.71,0:09:04.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She's glaring daggers at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.75,0:09:08.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think she's glaring at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.84,0:09:10.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's a hateful glare!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.34,0:09:13.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When she's smiling, she's at her scariest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.38,0:09:16.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was only a little smack talk! Let it slide!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.43,0:09:18.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I treated you to a taiyaki, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.36,0:09:34.40,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I had such high hopes in Father's will...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.20,0:09:40.70,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Last night, after solving an annoying puzzle \Nhe left, I found a box of his effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.58,0:09:43.66,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I finally got it open,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.08,0:09:48.92,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,all it contained was what looked like a \Nsmashed-up catalyst and this pendant.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.46,0:09:53.09,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, all the clocks in the house went crazy...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.09,0:09:59.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing in its own right,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.76,0:10:04.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but it won't help me summon Saber, \Nthe most powerful Servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.39,0:10:10.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,According to that dubious priest's information, \Nonly two more Masters are left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.32,0:10:12.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I don't have time to mope and worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.68,0:10:43.01,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have one message, recorded on \NJanuary 31, 3:21 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.56,0:10:45.02,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.60,0:10:49.55,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I'm sure you are aware, \Ntomorrow is the deadline, Rin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.36,0:10:53.50,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I insist that you start taking this seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.78,0:10:56.11,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Only two slots remain,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.11,0:10:59.41,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the Archer and the Saber classes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.41,0:11:02.26,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The ranks of the Masters must \Nbe filled without delay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.95,0:11:06.91,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Summon your Servant, and establish \Nyour Command Seals immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.91,0:11:12.66,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, if you are not participating in the \NHoly Grail War, that is a different matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.25,0:11:16.06,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you value your life, seek shelter \Nwith the Mages Associ—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.88,0:11:21.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know what I have to do. \NYou don't have to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.99,0:11:42.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Preparations, ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.91,0:11:44.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Time, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.70,0:11:46.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wavelength, ideal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.20,0:11:51.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By performing the summoning at 2 AM, \Nwhen my mana's at its peak,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.37,0:11:54.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get Saber, even without a catalyst!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.34,0:12:04.43,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For the elements, silver and iron.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.43,0:12:07.52,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For the foundation, stone and \Nthe Archduke of Contracts.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.52,0:12:10.50,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For the ancestor, my great master, Schweinorg.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.06,0:12:12.90,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Close the gates of the cardinal directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.90,0:12:16.75,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth from the Crown, and follow \Nthe forked road leading to the Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.86,0:12:23.53,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fill, fill, fill, fill, fill.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.20,0:12:26.16,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Repeat five times.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.41,0:12:29.00,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But when each is filled, destroy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.25,0:12:30.27,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Set.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.04,0:12:32.33,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Heed my words.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.71,0:12:37.02,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My will creates your body, and your \Nsword creates my destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.96,0:12:42.78,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you heed the Grail's call and obey my \Nwill and reason, then answer me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.01,0:12:45.76,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hereby swear...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.76,0:12:48.77,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That I shall be all the good in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.77,0:12:51.73,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That I shall defeat all evil in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.31,0:12:55.19,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You seven heavens, clad in the \Nthree great words of power,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.19,0:12:56.96,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,come forth from the circle of binding...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.96,0:12:58.79,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Guardian of the Scales!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.08,0:13:13.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That was flawless!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.54,0:13:16.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know I drew the most powerful card!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.38,0:13:22.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.38,0:13:25.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The door's broken...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.39,0:13:26.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.07,0:13:49.62,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, all the clocks in the house \Nwere an hour fast today...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.91,0:13:52.62,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Which means it's now 1 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.62,0:13:53.39,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not 2 AM?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.21,0:13:56.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I did it again!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.33,0:13:58.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's done is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.17,0:14:01.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you give me that task, Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.76,0:14:05.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well? What are you supposed to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.38,0:14:08.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's the first thing you say to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.51,0:14:12.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Seems I've been drawn by quite \Nthe unusual little Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.56,0:14:13.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.77,0:14:15.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or was it I who drew the short straw?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.44,0:14:18.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just to make sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.02,0:14:21.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're my Servant, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.36,0:14:25.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And are you my Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.03,0:14:27.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I was summoned, you weren't present.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.99,0:14:29.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't a baby bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.66,0:14:34.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't joke and make it sound like you imprint on \Nyour Master when you first open your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.79,0:14:36.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.75,0:14:43.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm simply asking if you really are \Nmy Servant, and no one else's.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.55,0:14:47.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master-Servant relationships should be \Nclearly laid out, right off the bat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.03,0:14:48.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.47,0:14:50.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am in complete agreement with that opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.85,0:14:55.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But where is the evidence that you are my Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.56,0:15:00.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here. This is all the proof you need \Nthat I am your Master, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.36,0:15:04.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.78,0:15:06.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really mean that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.40,0:15:11.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't that meaningless token I wanted to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.32,0:15:15.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to see if you are someone \Nworthy of my loyalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.54,0:15:16.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.54,0:15:19.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not good enough to be your Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.83,0:15:24.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am utterly dissatisfied, but I do \Nacknowledge you as my Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.71,0:15:27.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But on one condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.55,0:15:30.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In the war to come, I will \Ndisregard anything you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.64,0:15:32.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will decide all battle policy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.30,0:15:35.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I trust you have no objections.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.35,0:15:38.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.06,0:15:43.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You grudgingly acknowledge me, but you \Nwon't listen to my opinions?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.36,0:15:44.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.28,0:15:47.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are my Servant, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.90,0:15:50.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but in form alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.49,0:15:53.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I will obey you in form alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.74,0:15:56.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But when fighting, I will call my own shots.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.95,0:16:01.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Until this Holy Grail War ends, I suggest \Nyou sit tight in the cellar or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.33,0:16:05.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That should keep even one as \Ninexperienced as you alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.01,0:16:09.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, have I made you angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.88,0:16:13.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I have nothing but \Nrespect for your office.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.14,0:16:16.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I was summoned to \Nwin victory for my Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.47,0:16:22.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My victory is your victory, and I will \Nyield any spoils of battle to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.77,0:16:25.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surely that will be agreeable?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.27,0:16:30.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, leave everything to me, \Nand see to your own wellbeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.24,0:16:32.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't expect
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.53,0:16:34.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,anything from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.03,0:16:37.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now I'm mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.99,0:16:41.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fine! If that's how you're going \Nto be, I'll use one on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.46,0:16:42.71,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anfang!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.71,0:16:43.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.58,0:16:44.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I would!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.21,0:16:47.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You lousy ingrate!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.21,0:16:49.59,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Vertrag... Ein neuer Nagel...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.76,0:16:52.63,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Ein neues Gesetz... Ein neues Gesetz...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.09,0:16:51.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, are you crazy, Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.97,0:16:54.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who would use a Command \NSeal on something so...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.63,0:16:54.68,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Ein neues Verbrechen!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.68,0:16:56.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.01,0:16:58.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're my Servant, got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.81,0:17:02.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That means absolute obedience \Nto everything I say!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.19,0:17:12.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you that impulsive, girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.24,0:17:15.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You would use a Command Seal \Nwith so broad an order?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.66,0:17:19.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,L-Let's take this elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.49,0:17:20.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.88,0:17:37.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe I have a fair understanding \Nof your disposition now, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.76,0:17:43.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just to be sure, you do realize how precious \Nthe Command Seals are, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.35,0:17:46.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's with his superior tone?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.52,0:17:49.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Absolute obedience," my butt...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.73,0:17:53.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They symbolize our power to compel \Nour Servants three times.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.15,0:17:54.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.62,0:17:56.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.57,0:18:01.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Command Seals compel a Servant \Nto perform an action.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.33,0:18:06.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For example, I am incapable of \Nteleporting far from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.62,0:18:09.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, if you were to use a \NCommand Seal and say, "Go,"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.90,0:18:12.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it would use mana from both of us, to accomplish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.92,0:18:14.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The three Command Seals are
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.91,0:18:18.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the crystallization of high magic and can \Novercome the limits of flesh and blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.60,0:18:22.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I suppose the number has \Nnow been reduced to two.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.27,0:18:24.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.60,0:18:27.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So what? I still have two.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.48,0:18:30.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The rule I ordered you to obey wasn't a waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.65,0:18:34.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I admit that I miscalculated.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.20,0:18:38.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When the order is vaguely worded, \NCommand Seals are less effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.99,0:18:42.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Which is exactly what happened \Nwith your earlier order.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.87,0:18:45.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even a hundred Command Seals could not compel
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.52,0:18:47.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,true, absolute obedience in every word and deed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.46,0:18:53.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then you're saying the Command \NSeal I used earlier was pointless?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.80,0:18:55.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, that would be the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.34,0:19:00.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it would seem your skill \Nas a mage is extraordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.14,0:19:02.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Extraordinary?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.72,0:19:05.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that is what I meant by "miscalculated."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.73,0:19:09.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your words now carry a powerful \Ncompulsion for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.79,0:19:10.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.48,0:19:13.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you getting at?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.53,0:19:17.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I take back what I said, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.74,0:19:21.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You may be young in years, but you \Nare an outstanding mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.99,0:19:27.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was mistaken in looking down on you as a \Nchild and trying to keep you from fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.92,0:19:31.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for both that and my poor manners.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.04,0:19:37.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then you acknowledge me as your Master, \Neven without my using a Command Seal?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.59,0:19:38.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.26,0:19:42.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd just been summoned, so I \Nwasn't yet fully acclimated.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.85,0:19:45.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But now, we are completely connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.52,0:19:50.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As a mage, you should be able to sense the \Nbond between us through our pact.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.61,0:19:59.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our pact...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.32,0:20:00.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.49,0:20:05.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Servants are summoned by the Holy Grail, \Nbut what anchors them to this world is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.47,0:20:06.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.54,0:20:08.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A Master's power.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.54,0:20:13.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A Servant is anchored to this world by \Nthe mana supplied by his Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.50,0:20:16.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My mana from you is more than satisfactory.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.88,0:20:20.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are a first-rate mage, no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.41,0:20:24.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's too late to score any points with flattery.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.35,0:20:29.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.27,0:20:30.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't Saber?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.60,0:20:34.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to disappoint, but I have no sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.40,0:20:36.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Which makes you Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.48,0:20:38.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Boy, I blew it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.03,0:20:41.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I used all those gems, and I \Nstill didn't get the Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.72,0:20:44.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, pardon me for not being the Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.91,0:20:50.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was a regrettable mistake, but I'm to blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.08,0:20:54.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make you rue those words.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.67,0:20:57.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And when the day comes, apologize all \Nyou want. I won't forgive you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.81,0:21:12.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,See to it that I regret my words, Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.19,0:21:14.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When you do, I'll make you let me apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.81,0:21:18.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. Don't forget that, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.25,0:21:36.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.50,0:21:38.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.04,0:21:39.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Which Heroic Spirit are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.49,0:21:43.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.64,0:21:49.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot give you any answers \Nregarding my identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.64,0:21:52.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For the simple reason that I do not know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.48,0:21:57.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's that supposed to mean? \NAre you messing with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.61,0:22:00.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mean to insult you, Master,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.11,0:22:02.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but it's the result of your imperfect summoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.99,0:22:04.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My memories are a jumble.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.16,0:22:07.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My name and origin are hazy, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.70,0:22:10.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Admittedly, those aren't important details,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.70,0:22:12.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so it's nothing to be concerned about.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.25,0:22:15.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm very concerned about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.25,0:22:19.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I don't know what Heroic Spirit you are, \NI don't know how powerful you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.38,0:22:21.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is a trivial matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.42,0:22:23.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You call that "trivial"?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.30,0:22:26.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I don't know how powerful my partner is, \NI can't formulate a strategy, can I?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.05,0:22:29.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.30,0:22:32.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am a Servant who was summoned by you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.10,0:22:33.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I could not be anything but the most powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.48,0:22:38.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.98,0:22:43.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It won't change the fact that no one \Nelse knows his true identity...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.19,0:22:46.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For the time being, we'll overlook \Nthe issue of your identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.11,0:22:49.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And now, Archer, your first job.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.20,0:22:51.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right down to business, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.74,0:22:53.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My Master is belligerent.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.87,0:22:54.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And who is my enemy—
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.79,0:22:59.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Clean the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.38,0:23:02.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You made that mess, so I expect \Nyou to make it spotless.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.34,0:23:04.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.38,0:23:06.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think Servants are?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.72,0:23:08.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Familiars, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.05,0:23:10.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,These talk back and are unruly, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.72,0:23:14.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.20,0:23:15.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you can go to hell, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.24,0:23:29.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.86,0:23:36.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The battle I've been awaiting for \Nten years is about to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.08,0:23:40.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My Holy Grail War...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.97,0:23:56.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is way beyond running late.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.73,0:23:58.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just skip school today.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.52,0:24:08.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right, it was Archer I summoned, not Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.82,0:24:13.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With the added bonus that \Nhe doesn't know who he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.95,0:24:17.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've got a headache, all of a sudden.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.25,0:24:22.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.79,0:24:25.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did the summoning drain all my mana?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.14,0:24:36.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he isn't so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.60,0:24:39.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The sun came up long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.77,0:24:43.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're quite the slob, aren't you, girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.32,0:24:53.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.31,0:24:56.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you smirking at?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.66,0:25:01.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, have you \Nremembered who you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.29,0:25:01.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.46,0:25:03.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.71,0:25:07.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll think of what to do about \Nyour amnesia in due time.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.84,0:25:09.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Get ready to go out, Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.96,0:25:12.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you around the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.43,0:25:17.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Before that, Master, aren't you \Nforgetting something important?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.02,0:25:20.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Something important?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.98,0:25:22.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good grief...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.67,0:25:27.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We have yet to carry out the most \Nimportant exchange of our pact.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.61,0:25:30.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The most important exchange of our pact?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.11,0:25:34.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Girl... You really aren't a \Nmorning person, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.86,0:25:36.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who do you think you are, \N"girl" this and "girl" that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.64,0:25:38.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.20,0:25:40.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Darn.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.41,0:25:41.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our names.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.58,0:25:43.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It finally clicked?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.25,0:25:46.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, Master... From now on, \Nwhat shall I call you?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.92,0:25:50.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Tohsaka Rin.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.63,0:25:52.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Call me whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.76,0:25:55.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will call you "Rin," then.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.76,0:25:58.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the sound of it suits you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.93,0:26:48.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think? Doesn't this place \Nhave a great view of the city?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.98,0:26:55.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we'd come here in the first place, \Nwe wouldn't have had to walk around all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.40,0:26:57.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.03,0:27:00.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All you get from up here is a \Npanoramic view of the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.28,0:27:03.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You can't get a feel for how a city is\Nlaid out unless you go places in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.08,0:27:05.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't quite true.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.12,0:27:08.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My class isn't called "Archer" for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.13,0:27:12.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Without excellent eyesight, \Nbowmen aren't much use.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.09,0:27:13.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.57,0:27:16.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can make out how many \Ntiles are on that bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.80,0:27:18.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm amazed.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.13,0:27:21.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Archer class really is made up of archers!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.43,0:27:22.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rin...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.76,0:27:27.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be that you're mocking me?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.23,0:27:29.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.78,0:27:36.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's him. I know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.74,0:27:39.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Have you spotted our enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.03,0:27:41.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, just an acquaintance.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.49,0:27:43.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,An ordinary person who has nothing to do with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.37,0:27:46.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I neglected to ask you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.41,0:27:47.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Which is?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.62,0:27:52.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rin, were you trained from an \Nearly age to be a Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.00,0:27:54.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And did you go along with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.71,0:27:55.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.07,0:28:00.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For generations, winning the Grail \Nhas been the Tohsaka dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.01,0:28:04.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then I expect that you know your goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.31,0:28:08.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unless I know your wish, I cannot \Nentrust my blades to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.69,0:28:10.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rin, what is your wish?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.48,0:28:12.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wish?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.56,0:28:14.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.32,0:28:15.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.82,0:28:17.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.94,0:28:21.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Grail is an omnipotent cup \Nthat can grant any wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.61,0:28:23.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It has the power to conquer \Nthe real world for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.41,0:28:27.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Conquering the world seems \Nlike a pain in the butt,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.20,0:28:30.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and there's no point in wishing \Nfor dumb things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.46,0:28:32.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I fail to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.63,0:28:34.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why, then, are you fighting?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.71,0:28:38.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because there's a battle to be fought, Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.92,0:28:41.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then you are...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.38,0:28:44.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm fighting to win. That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.35,0:28:47.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.77,0:28:51.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are indeed my ideal Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.56,0:28:54.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There can be no doubt that you \Nare the perfect Master for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.40,0:28:57.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is no one else whom I could hope to serve.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.07,0:28:59.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey—
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.84,0:29:24.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rin? Why are you hiding?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.97,0:29:26.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's someone I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.18,0:29:30.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I skipped school today, so I don't \Nwant to run into anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.67,0:29:56.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Kirei? It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.63,0:30:02.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I made a pact with Archer last night, \Nso please list me officially as a Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.13,0:30:03.11,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.43,0:30:05.09,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then, what are your plans?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.09,0:30:08.05,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Would you care to stop by?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.05,0:30:10.87,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have something for you that \Nyour parents left in my care.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.52,0:30:13.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You mean Father's will?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.27,0:30:17.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I already deciphered it and found \Nwhat he left, so that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.86,0:30:20.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll stop by if I'm ever in the mood, \Nso I'll see you then.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.36,0:30:22.53,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Rin—
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.20,0:30:26.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to school?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.74,0:30:27.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.66,0:30:28.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.87,0:30:31.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, but isn't a school
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.26,0:30:34.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,a location where it would be difficult \Nto prepare for surprise attacks?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.54,0:30:39.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We avoid public battles with \Nother Masters, don't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.13,0:30:41.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I think if we're somewhere as public as a school,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.66,0:30:44.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,there's little chance of a sneak attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.47,0:30:46.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Purely hypothetically,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.05,0:30:49.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,if there is an enemy in this haven, \Nwhat will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.89,0:30:51.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That won't happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.72,0:30:56.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's only one mage family in \Nthis city besides the Tohsaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.64,0:30:59.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That family is a shadow of its former self.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.48,0:31:01.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They could never produce a Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.69,0:31:06.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then what you're saying is that there is \Nindeed another mage at your school.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.42,0:31:10.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But this person possesses insufficient \Nmana to ever become a Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.95,0:31:12.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.45,0:31:16.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nevertheless, Rin, there is an \Nexception to everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.54,0:31:21.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If a mage you're unaware of is at the school...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.10,0:31:36.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is more than just stale air...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.94,0:31:39.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Has a magical barrier already been established?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.98,0:31:41.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not fully.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.56,0:31:44.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But preparations seem to be well underway.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.69,0:31:48.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To act so boldly, this person \Nis either a heavy hitter...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.45,0:31:50.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or a complete novice.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.70,0:31:53.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If a bounded field can be sensed by \Nothers, that's a third-rate hack.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.37,0:31:58.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A first-rate mage stays hidden \Nuntil they're ready to strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.67,0:32:00.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is your plan, Rin?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.83,0:32:04.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't give a damn whether this \Nperson's first-rate or third-rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.30,0:32:09.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whoever started to put up crude garbage \Nlike this in my territory gets taken out!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.26,0:32:11.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Archer...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.37,0:32:13.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After school, we'll start by examining the barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.97,0:32:17.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's decide whether to remove or leave it \Nonce we determine what kind of field it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.15,0:32:25.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll talk later, Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.24,0:32:29.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let me help you, Sakura.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.62,0:32:31.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka-senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.66,0:32:35.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.04,0:32:37.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.87,0:32:40.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, are you taking these to your class?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.42,0:32:42.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To Kuzuki-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.50,0:32:45.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He said there was a typo, so he \Nwas taking them all back.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.50,0:32:47.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Kuzuki-sensei is a perfectionist, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.56,0:33:05.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This makes seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.65,0:33:08.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, this one seems to be the trigger point.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.53,0:33:11.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen, or even heard of, writing like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.70,0:33:13.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Darn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.16,0:33:15.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is way over my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.95,0:33:18.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer, you can sense the \Nbarrier's nature, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.50,0:33:21.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If this barrier is activated,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.96,0:33:25.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it will cause every human inside \Nit to literally dissolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.75,0:33:27.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is soul-eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.71,0:33:30.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A fortress of blood that will dissolve
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.10,0:33:34.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,any human body within the field, \Nand harvest the souls oozing out.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.22,0:33:38.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And as for who, or what, might want souls, \Nthe obvious answer is a Servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.97,0:33:43.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer, would your kind do such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.56,0:33:45.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You surmise correctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.61,0:33:48.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fundamentally, we are non-corporeal beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.23,0:33:53.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just as your kind partakes of meat as nourishment, \NServants partake of minds and souls.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.82,0:33:59.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the more ingested, \Nthe greater the mana stores.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.74,0:34:03.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning that they aren't satisfied with \Nthe mana their Master is supplying?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.62,0:34:07.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that they aren't satisfied, \Nbut that more is always better.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.29,0:34:12.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To absorb energy from nearby humans \Nis a basic stratagem of a Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.30,0:34:16.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In that sense, this barrier is highly effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.22,0:34:18.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I feel aggravated.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.01,0:34:20.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Never say such a thing again, Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.64,0:34:22.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.02,0:34:24.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I would never do something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.52,0:34:28.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's erase it, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.27,0:34:31.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I may not completely undo it, but I \Ncan throw a wrench in the works.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.44,0:34:33.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What, you're going to erase it?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.40,0:34:34.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What a waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.88,0:34:51.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is this your handiwork?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.46,0:34:53.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.59,0:34:56.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stooping to dirty tricks is a mage's role.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.76,0:35:00.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My kind simply fights when and where we're told.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.47,0:35:04.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right, my invisible buddy?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.81,0:35:07.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you can see Archer...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.65,0:35:08.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're a Servant!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.40,0:35:14.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And if you know that, little girl, \Ncan I assume you're my enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.70,0:35:23.10,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fenced in on four sides... \NFighting here, we're at a disadvantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.45,0:35:26.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.33,0:35:29.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You seem ignorant, but you have the gist of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.75,0:35:32.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Boy, I really blew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.17,0:35:34.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't have let curiosity...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.93,0:35:40.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...get the better of me and spoken up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.06,0:35:50.56,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Es ist groß.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.56,0:35:51.94,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Es ist klein!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.82,0:35:56.28,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Vox Gott Es Atlas!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.57,0:36:03.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer, handle the landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.85,0:36:27.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.57,0:36:37.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now that's more like it!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.15,0:36:40.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm okay with people who get \Nright down to business!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.95,0:36:42.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lancer-class Servant!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.95,0:36:44.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.33,0:36:47.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your Servant doesn't strike me as a Saber, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.83,0:36:50.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.71,0:37:00.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You don't seem like the proper, \Nsingle-combat type, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.76,0:37:02.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, an Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.14,0:37:06.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Go on, take out your bow, Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.72,0:37:08.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wait for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.35,0:37:12.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.90,0:37:18.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's he...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.69,0:37:21.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer, you'll get no assistance from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.65,0:37:24.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right here and now, show me what you've got!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.43,0:37:52.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.05,0:38:21.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So this is a battle between Servants...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.52,0:38:35.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That was stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.48,0:38:38.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.37,0:38:49.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A dual wielder, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.25,0:39:03.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A mere bowman who thinks \Nhe's a swordsman, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.41,0:39:28.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Twenty-seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.16,0:39:31.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To think I've disarmed you twenty-seven \Ntimes, yet you still have more.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.24,0:39:35.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter? This wait-and-see \Napproach isn't like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.37,0:39:37.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where'd all that spirit go?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.96,0:39:41.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Trying to provoke me, you sly old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.42,0:39:43.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, I'll ask the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.46,0:39:45.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What land's Heroic Spirit are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.67,0:39:48.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've never heard of a bowman \Nwho wields two swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.68,0:39:51.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You, on the other hand, are easily identifiable.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.51,0:39:54.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They say that only the swiftest heroes \Nare chosen to be spearmen,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.52,0:39:57.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and you stand head-and-shoulders above them.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.31,0:40:00.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There aren't even three spearmen \Nof your skill in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.90,0:40:04.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Add in a beast's agility, and that leaves but one.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.99,0:40:07.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You flatter me, Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.66,0:40:19.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then, will you face my mightiest blow?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.92,0:40:22.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't stop you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.38,0:40:24.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are an enemy I must overcome eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.92,0:40:26.26,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.63,0:40:28.80,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That massive amount of mana...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.80,0:40:31.49,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's clearly about to use his Noble Phantasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.18,0:40:33.57,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If he attacks...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.50,0:40:39.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.12,0:40:43.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A student?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.15,0:40:45.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Someone was still in the school building?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.19,0:40:46.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So it would seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.53,0:40:48.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It saved my life, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.57,0:40:51.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, where did Lancer go?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.07,0:40:52.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He chased after that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.58,0:40:57.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's a witness, so he probably \Nwent to eliminate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.16,0:40:59.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Follow them, Archer!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.37,0:41:01.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll catch up!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.17,0:41:04.59,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it, that was so stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.05,0:41:07.19,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Eliminating witnesses is the first rule for mages.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.63,0:41:11.01,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hated that rule, so I've always been extra careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.84,0:41:48.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer, follow Lancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.21,0:41:53.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't at least learn his Master's face, \Nnone of this will have been worth it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.89,0:42:02.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rin, this is your responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.40,0:42:10.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lancer pierced him with his spear...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.94,0:42:13.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If his heart was hit, there's no way to save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.31,0:42:20.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.75,0:42:23.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll sit with you until your time comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.09,0:42:37.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do this to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.22,0:42:39.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.35,0:42:43.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you have to pick this hour, \Non this day, to be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.14,0:42:47.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How am I supposed to look \Nher in the eye tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.28,0:42:58.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's still a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.30,0:43:20.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but I failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.56,0:43:23.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This Master is very cautious.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.77,0:43:25.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.06,0:43:27.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I shouldn't have expected \Nit to be that easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.69,0:43:34.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You went to get it for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.24,0:43:41.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't lose it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.12,0:43:43.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't suit anyone but you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.66,0:43:44.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You think?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.95,0:43:46.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.00,0:43:50.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Like I thought, there doesn't seem \Nto be any mana left in it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.34,0:43:52.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.71,0:43:54.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Rin?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.34,0:43:59.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When Lancer's Master learns the witness \Nthey thought they'd killed is still alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.93,0:44:03.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He'll probably send Lancer back to finish the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.73,0:44:13.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't your burden to bear...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.78,0:44:17.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After what it cost me to save him, \NI'm not about to let him die!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.41,0:44:19.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's here...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.20,0:44:20.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Lancer-class Servant!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.74,0:44:25.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Rin!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.91,0:44:27.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sensing more than one Servant!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.86,0:44:54.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Saber-class Servant...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.72,0:47:26.89,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Trace on.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.89,0:47:29.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're an early riser, Tohsaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.01,0:47:30.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Still, there should be a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.35,0:47:33.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I need to live, to fulfill my duties.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.35,0:47:36.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I don't hurry and call someone, you'll die.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.00,0:47:37.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Seventh Servant?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.31,0:47:39.99,Next,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(489,1)}Next Time \NWinter Days, A Fateful Night
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.35,0:47:40.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you my Master?
